	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New Orleans&#44; La.</placeName> <date>July 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1847</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd. I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dr Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Circumstances of an unavoidable<lb/> nature in my affairs having induced me to remove from <placeName>Columbia&#44;<lb/> So. Ca.</placeName> Since the <date>1st January</date> last&#44; and now being permanently<lb/> located in this city&#44; I am desirous of receiving the future<lb/> numbers of the &#8220;Occident&#8221; directed to me&#44; &#8220;care <persName>Messrs.<lb/> E. I. Hart &#38; Co.</persName> <placeName>New Orleans&#44; La.</placeName>&#8221;&#8212;  you will please for&#45;<lb/>&#45;ward me No. 3 of fourth vol. For <date>June 1846</date>&#44; and at the same<lb/> time inform me of my indebtedness to you&#44; when <hi rend="underline">in the<lb/> course of next fall</hi> the amount shall be remitted or sub&#45;<lb/>&#45;ject to your order</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">In hopes my request will be attended to</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I remain Resptfy yrs</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">Emanuel Sampson</persName></p>
				<p>P.S.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Permit me here to record a worthy act of <add>an</add> esteemed<lb/> Israelite&#44; that should not pass unnoticed&#44; but whose example might<lb/> well be followed by our wealthy brethren situated in places<lb/> as isolated&#44; &#40;as far as Judaism is concerned&#44;&#41; as the place where it<lb/> transpired&#44; with honor to themselves&#44; and the happy reflection<lb/> that they have been the humble instruments through which<lb/> T.O.</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p><hi rend="underline">another</hi> ordinance of the God of <placeName>Israel</placeName> has been carried out&#44;<lb/> I refer to <hi rend="underline"><persName>Joseph J. Andrews&#44; Esq.</persName> Of <placeName>Memphis&#44; Tenn</placeName></hi>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">A few months ago my family were on a visit<lb/> to <placeName>Memphis</placeName>&#44; where the Destroying Angel deprived me of<lb/> my first born&#44; a promising Boy of 2 years old&#44; when<lb/> <persName>Mr. Andrews</persName> called on the family &#40;the writer being in this<lb/> city at the time&#41; and very kindly informed them that<lb/> he had appropriated a tract of land for a <hi rend="underline">Jewish</hi><lb/> <hi rend="underline">Burial Ground</hi> for all Israelites who may hereafter<lb/> require the right of sepulchre in <placeName>Memphis</placeName>&#44; &#40;previous to<lb/> which time they had no separate ground&#41;&#59; they declined ac&#45;<lb/>&#45;cepting of the generous offer&#44; being desirous of removing<lb/> the remains of my child to this city for interment in<lb/> the Portuguese <add>Jewish</add> Burial Ground&#44; where it now lies&#8212;Since<lb/> which time I am informed that the ground in <placeName>Memphis</placeName> has<lb/> been neatly enclosed at the expense of <persName>Mr. Andrews</persName>&#44; and<lb/> the remains of a young German Israelite recently deceased&#44;<lb/> interred therein&#8212;Had it been out of my power to<lb/> remove the corpse of my child&#44; I should have had the<lb/> melancholy satisfaction of knowing that at least it was<lb/> deposited in ground sacred to Israelites.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Not having observed any notice on the subject in<lb/> the &#8220;Occident&#8221;&#44; I have thought it a duty to suggest to you<lb/> the propriety of putting it in such a form that it may<lb/> have a beneficial effect</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Very Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Yrs</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">E Sampson</persName></p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><hi rend="underline">Paid</hi></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
